text: The Malleco spiny-chest frog (Alsodes vittatus) is a frog. It lives in Chile. ==Home== Scientists are not sure whether this frog lives in forests, grassy places, or other places. They found it near small streams. Scientists saw this frog between 1000 and 1610 meters above sea level. ==Danger== Scientists say they do not know if this frog is in danger of dying out. Human beings change forests to grow pine trees, but scientists are not sure if the frogs live in those forests. ==First paper== * ==References== Category:Frogs of South America
title: Alsodes vittatus
